title: Novak Djokovic wins 23rd Grand Slam title by beating Casper Ruud in the French Open
description: Novak Djokovic has won his men’s-record 23rd Grand Slam title with a 7-6 (1), 6-3, 7-5 victory over Casper Ruud in the French Open final

title: Hospitalized Pope Francis follows Mass on TV
description: Pope Francis has followed his doctors' advice and skipped his customary Sunday noon public blessing as he convalesces from abdominal surgery

title: Environmental officials kill moose after it wanders onto Connecticut airport
description: Environment officials in Connecticut killed a moose Friday after it wandered onto the grounds at a Connecticut airport

title: Portion of I-95 collapses in Philadelphia, all lanes closed
description: A portion of Interstate 95 has collapsed in Philadelphia following a large vehicle fire, according to authorities.

title: Plurality of Americans support second Trump indictment: POLL
description: While a plurality of Americans supports the second Trump indictment, a familiar partisan divide has reemerged, polling shows.

title: Gunfire into funeral procession in suburban Chicago wounds 4, police say
description: Police say shots were fired into vehicles as a funeral procession passed through a Chicago suburb, badly wounding two people and hurting two others

title: Strong earthquake rattles northern Japan; no damage reported
description: A magnitude 6.2 earthquake has shaken Japan’s northernmost main island of Hokkaido

title: IS militants kill 2 Iraqi soldiers, wound 3 others in northern Iraq, officials say
description: Iraq’s security media office says Islamic State group militants have attacked an Iraqi army position in the northern governorate of Kirkuk, killing two military officers and wounding three soldiers

title: 6 injured in shooting outside Houston nightclub, police say
description: Six people were injured in a shooting in a parking lot of a nightclub in Houston, Chief Troy Finner said in a press conference Sunday morning.

title: Shootout in northwest Pakistan, along Afghan border, kills 3 soldiers, 3 militants, army says
description: Pakistan's army says militants attacked a security checkpoint in the country's northwest, along the border with Afghanistan, triggering a shootout that left three soldiers and three militants dead

title: Trump pledges to endorse Mark Robinson for North Carolina governor
description: Former President Donald Trump has pledged to endorse Republican Lt. Gov. Mark Robinson for North Carolina governor
